<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="396" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1045,1313]" pageId="0" pageNumber="396">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1114,1139]" pageId="0" pageNumber="396">
<emphasis box="[151,268,1114,1138]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="396" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
­
</emphasis>
Body small. Fastigium verticis shovel-shaped and flat, with a indistinct longitudinal sulcus in the midline, protruding forward, base slightly broad, tapering apically, apex rounded. Tegmina developed, surpassing apices of hind femora; hind wings longer than tegmina. Male tenth abdominal tergite elongated backward; cercus stout, inner side of base with one process, apex with or without divergence; subgenital plate with styli; genitalia sclerotized. Female cercus short and conical. Ovipositor moderately upcurved, apex of ventral valvula with a apical hook. Subgenital plate almost quadrilateral, base slightly broad, tapering apically, apex rounded.
</paragraph>
